card.note: May you always remember the special things about each other that made you fall in love.
card.author: All my love, Mom Randolph

card.note: Have two TV's! Remember forgiveness, patience and the love that brought you together. Marriage is best job you can and you get as much out of it as you put into it. Terry, let her decorate the house. You decorate the garage. (Tony's wisdom)
card.author: Talbert's

card.note: Advise handed down to us by our parents and in turn we gave to our children upon marriage: your spouse is your best friend. Respect, honor and never go to bed upset with each other.
card.author: Bill and Louise Berry

card.note: Wishing you the BEST on your Wedding Day and for many years to come! You two are the perfect pair, and I can't wait to see all of the wonderful things that the future has in store for you! Hopefully we will be able to live near each other again someday! Love you guys!!!
card.author: Daneel McDaniel

card.note: Never go to sleep angry with each other. Move on, let whatever it is go and always kiss good night. Tomorrow's a brand new day!
card.author: Ellen Ryan

card.note: To Keep Marriage Brimming/RWith love in the marriage cup,/RWhenever you're wrong, admit it;/RWhenever you're right, shut up.
card.author: Byron and Carla Wilkenfeld

card.note: Love is the most precious gift you will receive in your life. Hold it dear to you, nurture it and let it blossom and you will receive true happiness. With all our love,
card.author: Dad and Linda

card.note: We wish you both a life full of happiness! Our advice is never stop creating memories together. Whether it's the big adventures, life's milestones, or the simple things, the importance is creating them together. Also, always remember the MSU bond that you two share.
card.author: Kat & Rob Eyers

card.note: Always look for a way to make each other smile!
card.author: Kat & Rob Eyers

card.note: You'll probably hear people tell you to never go to bed angry but sometimes your just tired and cranky so go to bed and start fresh the next morning with hugs and kisses!
card.author: Jewels Watson

card.note: Cassi and Terry-/RI am so happy for you! My advice is that relationships are about compromise. So Terry, remember to compromise and realize that Cassi is always right :)
card.author: Jerica

card.note: You are a wonderful fit for each other. We are so happy for you both! Our snippet of wisdom is to talk out your differences, no matter how uncomfortable it is at the moment. You might not resolve it at that time, but you will be upfront & honest with each other.
card.author: Kim & Tony

card.note: Celebrate the strengths of your partner, but also be tolerant and understanding of their weaknesses. These will change over the years and yours will change as well./R/RWishing you sunshine and rainbows....and a long and loving marriage.
card.author: Romi and Barry Lewis

card.note: Many ingredients are needed to have a successful and happy life together...a cup of honest communication, a cup of supportiveness, a cup of learning to fight fairly, and 3 cups of love, patience, forgiveness and laughter.
card.author: Much love, Don and Laura Butts

card.note: "None are so old as those who have outlived enthusiasm."/RHenry David Thoreau (1817-1862),USA/R/RLaugh, love, live everyday as if it's your last. Dana (1956- )
card.author: Dana aka Mom/Mother-in-law

card.note: Dear Cassi and Terry, I wish for you all the happiness, blessings and fortune in your life together. I can see the love you have for each other and I know that it will continue to grow through the years.
card.author: Patricia Garcia

card.note: We totally love you both. We have had some good times and there will be lots more. You will always be in our hearts and have a safe place with us. Love Bob and Gretchen
card.author: Bob and Gretchen Evans
